Gauteng Health MEC Bandile Masuku has been fired. Masuku has been implicated in a dodgy PPE procurement tender. Gauteng Premier David Makhura announced Masuku's axed. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Premier David Makhura has made it clear that Dr Bandile Masuku hasn't been found guilty of corruption. Masuku has been implicated in a dodgy PPE procurement tender. READ: COVID-19 corruption: 'Independent report' clears the Masukus' Makhura says investigations into alleged PPE corruption are still ongoing. "With regards to the substantive public interest issue of whether the MEC was involved in acts of corruption or collusion, the SIU has reported to me that this investigation is ongoing." On Friday, Makhura announced that Masuku has been relieved of his duties. “The SIU has found that Health MEC, Dr Bandile Masuku, has failed to execute his functions in compliance with the constitution and the Public Finance Management Act (PFMA)," Makhura said. “In that regard, the SIU has recommended that the Premier take administrative action against the MEC for the purpose of determining the suitability to hold office as MEC for Health."